Midterm Lab 2: Travelling SalesMan Problem
Student: Kalambakal Josh Aron

Project Goal
The assignment required me to develop software which would display Cavite's location network and find the most efficient traveling route between all locations. The assessment of efficiency requires three specific measurements which include distance and time and fuel consumption.

Design and Implementation
Graph Representation:
The network of locations was represented as a Directed Graph (DiGraph) through the use of networkx library. The method was chosen because transportation systems typically need to follow predetermined routes. The graph's edges store data from the table which includes three attributes: Distance (km) and Time (mins) and Fuel (Liters).

Algorithm:
The program uses Dijkstra's Algorithm to find the shortest path. The algorithm works best for determining the least expensive route between nodes in a weighted graph. The system performs dynamic calculations because weight values change according to user selection of distance or time or fuel.

User Interface:
The interface was created through the use of Dash and Plotly. The system creates a web dashboard which allows users to select their starting and ending locations from dropdown fields. The map displays the selected route in real time while showing complete trip details.

Technical Requirements
Language: Python 3.13
Libraries: dash, dash_bootstrap_components, networkx, plotly
Users can access the program through a web browser at the following URL http://127.0.0.1:8050 while the script continues to operate.

Execution Instructions
Step 1: Install the necessary packages using:
pip install dash dash-bootstrap-components networkx pandas

Step 2: Run the script:
